For the cultivation of coriander plantation, plow the field with horizontal and make a flat flask of 3 × 2 m. Mix 8 to 10 kg of good rotten fenugreek in each span and mix it. If the waft flattens, it will be like a B. B should be covered with soil and provide light water. If weeds are high in excess, then after 15-20 cm distance in flat squats, sill the shallow lines and sow the seed and then cover the soil. Soak the steam well before sowing during summer season. And sow the seed after the arrival of wafa. For cottage cultivation, the seed requirement is 60-80 kg. Before sowing, it is necessary to process seeds for good germination. Before separation, separate seeds by squeezing coriander or wooden straw for separation of seeds. Before sowing, keep the boss for 12 hours in a warm place in water and then use it for cultivation. Therefore, germination increases by 8 to 10 days instead of 15 to 20 days and improves the production of coriander and helps in early recovery.

  In this treatment, the irrigation is withheld 45 days prior to the flowering.
This facilitates the shedding of leaves.
  Spray Ethrel 2 to 2.5ml/lit of water for leaf shedding
The trees are then medium pruned 40-45 days after withholding irrigation.
The recommended doses of fertilizers are applied immediately after pruning and irrigation is resumed. This leads to flowering and fruiting.
